# --- Web (Vite) env ---
# API base URL (defaults to http://localhost:3001/api when unset).
VITE_API_URL="http://localhost:3001/api"

# Google Maps browser key (Maps JavaScript API). Drop a real key here and the live
# tracking map + provider pin + ETA light up automatically — no code change needed.
# Leave empty to fall back to the graceful live-status card.
#
# SECURITY — this MUST be a different key from the API's GOOGLE_MAPS_SERVER_KEY.
# Vite inlines this value into the public JS bundle, so anyone can read it off the
# deployed site. The only thing stopping a scraped key from being used to bill your
# Google account is a key restriction, and browser and server keys need incompatible
# restriction types — so one key cannot safely serve both:
#   • This browser key: Google Cloud → Credentials → the key → Application restrictions
#     = "Websites", allow only your site's domains. API restrictions = Maps JavaScript API.
#   • The server key (apps/api/.env): Application restrictions = "IP addresses", allow only
#     your API server's egress IP. API restrictions = Geocoding API.
# Also set a billing budget + quota caps — a leaked unrestricted key is billable.
VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_KEY=""
